ial integrity, transactions, locks, and check constraints. Designed for professionals, workshop settings, and self-learners, the book demonstrates several databases so the reader can follow along in a hands-on approach. Each chapter also has a set of questions and follow up projects to reinforce comprehension of the material. FEATURES:Includes demonstration and solution implementations on the major Database Management Systems (MySQL, Oracle, and Microsoft SQL Server) and computing platforms (Linux/UNIX, MacOS, Windows) to be applicable for nearly every student and professionalEnd of chapter exercises to enhance comprehension of topics  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aComputer security. 0aDatabase security. 4aData. 4aE-Commerce. 4aIT Management & Security. 7aCOMPUTERS / Electronic Commerce (see also headings under BUSINESS & ECONOMICS / ECommerce).2bisacsh  aLinux/UNIX.  aMacOS.  aMicrosoft SQL Server.  aMySQL.  aOracle.  aWindows.  acomputer science.  acybersecurity.  adata analytics.  adata science.  adatabase normalization.  ae-commerce.  areferential integrity.  atransactions.0 cEPUBz97816839266100 cprintz978168392663440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168392662740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781683926627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781683926627/original  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles